1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,317
There is no establishing shot. We are close to him, and the

2
00:00:08,367 --> 00:00:12,683
only light is the fire. An old hand, bloody to the wrist,

3
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:17,050
closes on the worn grip of a sword. The blade is old

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:21,417
and notched in a hundred places, and on one finger sits a

5
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:25,783
heavy gold signet, its mark almost rubbed smooth. The blade goes forward

6
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:30,150
into a man we never see, and a shape twists away into

7
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:34,517
the dark. On one side there is fire, and men keep coming

8
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:38,883
out of it. The old hand turns the sword to meet them,

9
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:43,250
and meets them again. For half a breath the view opens: an

10
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:47,617
old man on dark ground, the smoke behind him lit saffron, the

11
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:51,983
blood to his elbow, more men closing in — and he does

12
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:56,350
not go down.

13
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:59,530
CUT TO BLACK.

14
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:03,121
A low government building the colour of the dust around it, the

15
00:01:03,171 --> 00:01:06,413
paint peeling off the board outside, a CBN jeep up on bricks

16
00:01:06,463 --> 00:01:09,704
with one wheel gone. A shared tempo pulls away in a cloud

17
00:01:09,754 --> 00:01:12,996
of grit and DEVA steps down with an iron trunk on his

18
00:01:13,046 --> 00:01:16,287
shoulder, his uniform still creased from the shop. He stands and takes

19
00:01:16,337 --> 00:01:19,579
the place in, and it is not what he pictured on the

20
00:01:19,629 --> 00:01:22,870
bus.

21
00:01:23,220 --> 00:01:27,010
Inside, a MUNSHI sits behind a register under a slow fan, a

22
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:30,850
glass of tea going cold by his elbow. He does not look

23
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:34,690
up when the door's shadow falls across his book.

24
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,470
Constable Deva. Transferred from Itarsi. I'm to report to Ratan Singh Panwar,

25
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:39,950
sir.

26
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:41,450
Sahib's out on rounds.

27
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:43,430
I see. When will he be back?

28
00:01:43,780 --> 00:01:45,570
He'll come.

29
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:48,990
Deva waits for more. There is no more. He sets the trunk

30
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:52,110
down, then thinks better of it and keeps standing.

31
00:01:52,460 --> 00:01:55,850
Should I... wait here? Or the quarters—

32
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,590
Sit.

33
00:01:57,940 --> 00:02:02,543
He sits on the bench. A KISAN comes in past him, a

34
00:02:02,593 --> 00:02:07,197
man who has been here before and knows the order of things.

35
00:02:07,247 --> 00:02:11,850
He lays a folded note on the open register and slides it

36
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:16,503
across without a word. The munshi takes it under his palm, stamps

37
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:21,157
a paper, and turns it around for the farmer to lift. It

38
00:02:21,207 --> 00:02:25,810
is done in seconds. The farmer touches his forehead and goes.

39
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:29,070
Deva watches the note go under the blotter, and is not sure

40
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:32,030
what he just saw.

41
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:34,090
That... what did he give that for?

42
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,430
Tea money.

43
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:36,690
For what, though?

44
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:39,030
The munshi looks up at him for the first time, then goes

45
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,070
back to his register.

46
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:45,690
Deva sits back down. He watches the stamped paper go out the

47
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:50,010
door in the farmer's hand, and says nothing.

48
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:53,803
RATAN comes in heavy and unhurried, the khaki gone shapeless on him,

49
00:02:53,853 --> 00:02:57,297
and lowers himself into the chair behind the desk as if it

50
00:02:57,347 --> 00:03:00,790
costs him something. Deva is on his feet at once.

51
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:03,970
Sir. Constable Deva. I've been posted under you.

52
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:07,374
Ratan looks at him — the new uniform, the open face —

53
00:03:07,424 --> 00:03:10,478
for a second longer than nothing, and then it is put away.

54
00:03:10,528 --> 00:03:13,582
He pulls the day's files toward him. A second KISAN is already

55
00:03:13,632 --> 00:03:16,686
at the desk, turning his cap in his hands, a thin file

56
00:03:16,736 --> 00:03:19,790
in front of him.

57
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:20,570
Yes.

58
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:24,150
Sir, the tractor turned over in the night, on my elder brother.

59
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:27,430
Just write that it was an accident. There's mourning at home, sir

60
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:30,710
— we want nothing else.

61
00:03:31,060 --> 00:03:35,010
Ratan opens the file. He does not read it. He signs.

62
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:40,510
Done. Go.

63
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:43,770
The farmer sets a small fold of notes by the inkpad and

64
00:03:43,820 --> 00:03:46,730
is gone before it lands. Ratan moves it under the blotter with

65
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:49,690
two fingers, the way the munshi did, without looking at it. Deva

66
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:52,650
has watched all of it.

67
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,870
Sir... won't there be a postmortem?

68
00:03:55,220 --> 00:03:55,810
For whom?

69
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:58,430
A man's dead, sir. At least take a look—

70
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,690
And what will looking get you?

71
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,830
...I don't know. But the rules—

72
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:06,010
Someone dies here every day. If I did a postmortem on each,

73
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:09,890
nothing else would ever get done.

74
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:14,190
He looks at Deva properly now, and does not look away as

75
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:18,190
fast as he might.

76
00:04:18,540 --> 00:04:19,930
You're from Itarsi, aren't you.

77
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:20,630
Yes, sir.

78
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:22,050
They don't grow opium there.

79
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,670
Opium? You mean... really?

80
00:04:25,020 --> 00:04:27,370
It's the crop here, on a government licence. The whole district runs

81
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:29,770
on it. Look too hard and the first thing you'll lose is

82
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:32,170
your job.

83
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:34,670
Deva does not answer. Ratan has already pulled the next file toward

84
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,870
him.

85
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:40,701
A narrow shop hung with other men's pledges — brass, a radio,

86
00:04:40,751 --> 00:04:44,233
a woman's set of bangles on a nail. The SAHUKAR sits behind

87
00:04:44,283 --> 00:04:47,764
a low counter with a small cloth bundle in front of him,

88
00:04:47,814 --> 00:04:51,296
which he does not open. Off to the side, on a stool,

89
00:04:51,346 --> 00:04:54,827
sits CHARAN — very old, one eye gone milky — who has

90
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:58,359
come, it seems, only to be in the room with the thing

91
00:04:58,409 --> 00:05:01,890
in the cloth.

92
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,070
The interest keeps mounting, Singh sahib. It's not me saying it —

93
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,950
the ledgers say it.

94
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:09,050
Ratan lays down what notes he has on the counter. The sahukar

95
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:11,850
looks at them, and does not pick them up.

96
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,590
This is barely half the interest.

97
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:14,930
The rest next month.

98
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:17,790
I hear the same thing every month, sahib. A jeweller came last

99
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,350
week. It's an old signet, the gold is heavy — he'll pay

100
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,910
well. I've held it back out of respect for you. But how

101
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:25,470
long?

102
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:29,930
Ratan says nothing. He looks at the cloth and not at it.

103
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:32,310
That signet is not a thing to be sold, seth.

104
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:34,290
Charan baba, don't start again.

105
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:38,363
That signet is heavy with the blood of ancestors, not with gold.

106
00:05:38,413 --> 00:05:42,137
Listen, son. They were of Raja Bhoj's line — Parmar, Panwar. Khilji's

107
00:05:42,187 --> 00:05:45,910
storm broke on this very soil, seven hundred years ago. The whole

108
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:49,683
fort fell. And one had his head severed from his body, and

109
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:53,457
still the sword kept moving. Fallen, he did not fall. That signet

110
00:05:53,507 --> 00:05:57,230
is from his finger.

111
00:05:57,580 --> 00:06:00,879
The sahukar has heard it before and looks away, embarrassed for the

112
00:06:00,929 --> 00:06:04,227
old man. Ratan has heard it before too. He does not turn

113
00:06:04,277 --> 00:06:07,576
around. He pushes the half-payment an inch further across the counter, the

114
00:06:07,626 --> 00:06:10,924
most he can do, and walks out into the light. For a

115
00:06:10,974 --> 00:06:14,273
moment his right hand hangs at his side — the finger where

116
00:06:14,323 --> 00:06:17,621
the ring used to sit is bare, with a pale band still

117
00:06:17,671 --> 00:06:20,970
on the skin.

118
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,963
A SIPAHI comes in off the road, dust to the knees, and

119
00:06:24,013 --> 00:06:26,657
puts a thin file on the desk — barely a page in

120
00:06:26,707 --> 00:06:29,350
it.

121
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:32,130
This morning, near Koteshwar, a girl was found at the edge of

122
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:34,610
a field, sir.

123
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:35,470
Whose?

124
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:38,730
From the big house. Must have fallen in the night, in the

125
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:41,690
dark. The family says settle it quickly — there's a wedding coming,

126
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:44,650
word mustn't spread.

127
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,590
Which big house?

128
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,330
Bherulal seth's.

129
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:50,790
The name means nothing to Ratan. He does not open the file.

130
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:53,950
Deva, beside him, looks down at the closed cover.

131
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:54,890
A girl, was it?

132
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,270
She was. Now she isn't.

133
00:06:57,620 --> 00:06:59,650
Put it on the pile.

134
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,137
Deva looks at the single thin page that is all there is

135
00:07:02,187 --> 00:07:04,323
of her. The sipahi sets the file on the day's pile and

136
00:07:04,373 --> 00:07:06,510
goes back out to the road.

137
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:10,437
The light has gone amber. The pile has come down to the

138
00:07:10,487 --> 00:07:14,063
last file, the thin one. Ratan opens the cover, reads to the

139
00:07:14,113 --> 00:07:17,690
end of the first line, and uncaps his pen.

140
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,630
Sir. Should we go and look, just once? Koteshwar's close. Half an

141
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,270
hour.

142
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:25,890
She fell.

143
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,870
You haven't even seen it, and—

144
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:29,450
There's the constable's report, isn't there.

145
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,750
But sir, it's a girl, it's a big house's matter — if

146
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,750
someone asks tomorrow—

147
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,010
No one will ask.

148
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:39,577
He says it flat, certain, the certainty of a man who knows

149
00:07:39,627 --> 00:07:43,843
exactly who asks questions in this district and who does not. He

150
00:07:43,893 --> 00:07:48,110
writes the cause across the form, caps the pen, and closes the

151
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:52,377
file without ever turning to the name on the second page. The

152
00:07:52,427 --> 00:07:56,643
day's fold of notes goes into his breast pocket. He stands, tired,

153
00:07:56,693 --> 00:08:00,910
and reaches for his cap.

154
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:05,010
Deva starts to say something and stops himself. He watches the day's

155
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:08,810
notes go into Ratan's pocket, and this time he stays quiet.

156
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:13,510
A small kept house, everything in its place and nothing new in

157
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:17,910
years. KANTA sets a plate in front of him and straightens, a

158
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:22,310
hand on her back. On the side table, an opened government envelope.

159
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:25,250
The pension papers came today. The office called as well. Two more

160
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,890
years.

161
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:31,523
Ratan sits. He turns his hand over and looks at the pale

162
00:08:31,573 --> 00:08:34,857
band where the ring used to be, then at the plate. He

163
00:08:34,907 --> 00:08:38,190
does not start eating.

164
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:41,970
Two years and you'll be home all day. I keep wondering what

165
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:45,450
you'll do with yourself. You were never one to sit at home.

166
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:49,030
I'll eat your cooking.

167
00:08:49,380 --> 00:08:52,690
Don't sweet-talk me. Eat — it's going cold.

168
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:56,203
He eats. She stands a moment longer than she needs to, looking

169
00:08:56,253 --> 00:08:59,417
at the top of his bent head from across the small kitchen,

170
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:02,630
across a distance that has grown over the years without either of

171
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:05,843
them deciding it. Then she takes the envelope off the side table

172
00:09:05,893 --> 00:09:09,057
and puts it away in a drawer, where the other unspoken things

173
00:09:09,107 --> 00:09:12,270
are kept.

174
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:16,501
The pyre has caught. Not many have come — a handful of

175
00:09:16,551 --> 00:09:20,433
old men, a son with his head freshly shaved, a dog keeping

176
00:09:20,483 --> 00:09:24,364
its distance. A singer works through a Nirgun bhajan, the kind sung

177
00:09:24,414 --> 00:09:28,296
where there is no idol and no comfort to be had from

178
00:09:28,346 --> 00:09:32,227
the words. RATAN stands at the edge with his hands behind his

179
00:09:32,277 --> 00:09:36,159
back. GOVIND, his own age, stands next to him and watches the

180
00:09:36,209 --> 00:09:40,090
fire instead of the body.

181
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,550
There were four of us, remember? You, me, him, and Kailash. Now

182
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,710
there are two left.

183
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:45,410
Mm.

184
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:49,123
Look how many came. Three months ago the man was in uniform,

185
00:09:49,173 --> 00:09:52,537
gave the orders. He retired, and everyone forgot. Today there aren't even

186
00:09:52,587 --> 00:09:55,950
enough to carry the pyre.

187
00:09:56,300 --> 00:10:00,463
Ratan watches the smoke go up and does not answer. Govind is

188
00:10:00,513 --> 00:10:04,677
quiet a while, then says the thing more softly, not to wound,

189
00:10:04,727 --> 00:10:08,890
just because it is in him.

190
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:12,443
Who'll remember us, Ratan? A few years, and we're this same ash.

191
00:10:12,493 --> 00:10:15,697
No son, no name — no one to ask what kind of

192
00:10:15,747 --> 00:10:18,950
man he was.

193
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:22,210
Ratan looks down at his own hands. He does not say anything.

194
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:25,870
The others have gone. The pyre is down to embers. Govind crouches

195
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:29,230
and feeds a last stick into it, more for something to do

196
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:32,590
than for the fire. Ratan stands as if he means to leave

197
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:35,950
and does not.

198
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:36,970
Remember Chambal?

199
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,190
Let it go now, Govind.

200
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:42,830
No, listen. When you went alone into the ravines, after those dacoits.

201
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:46,170
The whole station stood outside, wetting their trousers, and you went in.

202
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:49,510
And by evening you brought them out tied up. Alone. Your photo

203
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:52,850
was in the paper.

204
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,790
That was many years ago. A different man.

205
00:10:56,140 --> 00:10:59,610
Exactly. You were different, Ratan. The rest of us joined for the

206
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:03,130
wages. There was something else in you. A man doesn't really change,

207
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:06,650
brother. He just gets buried, on top. The earth covers him. But

208
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:10,170
underneath, he's the same.

209
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:14,406
Ratan looks at his hands again. Govind lets it sit; he has

210
00:11:14,456 --> 00:11:18,342
said it before and he will say it again, and they both

211
00:11:18,392 --> 00:11:22,278
know it. Ratan turns to go. At the road, where one way

212
00:11:22,328 --> 00:11:26,214
runs home and the other toward Koteshwar, he stands a moment. Then

213
00:11:26,264 --> 00:11:30,150
he takes the road to Koteshwar.

214
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:34,482
The place has been walked over by everyone who came to look

215
00:11:34,532 --> 00:11:38,514
and to settle it — sandal-prints, a tractor's tread, the dragged smear

216
00:11:38,564 --> 00:11:42,546
where they lifted her. A few villagers stop their work to watch

217
00:11:42,596 --> 00:11:46,578
the old inspector who never comes to a scene now standing at

218
00:11:46,628 --> 00:11:50,610
one, in no hurry, looking at the dirt.

219
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,630
Who found her?

220
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:54,290
A young CHARVAHA (herder), hanging back, answers because Ratan is looking at

221
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:56,650
him.

222
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,310
I did, sir. In the morning, I'd brought the buffalo. She was

223
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,670
lying right here.

224
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:02,930
Which way was she facing?

225
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:06,110
Face down. Below the bund.

226
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:09,810
Ratan crouches at the bund and puts his hand flat on top

227
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:13,210
of it. It comes up to his knee. He looks at it

228
00:12:13,260 --> 00:12:16,610
a long time. He looks at the dry, hard earth, and at

229
00:12:16,660 --> 00:12:20,010
the distance to the well across the field, and at the bund

230
00:12:20,060 --> 00:12:23,410
again. He has not worked a scene in twenty-five years. He works

231
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:26,810
this one.

232
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:31,510
A bund knee-high.

233
00:12:31,860 --> 00:12:33,090
Sir?

234
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:37,070
Nothing.

235
00:12:37,420 --> 00:12:41,290
A older KISAN, sensing the wrong kind of attention coming to the

236
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:45,210
village, speaks up, helpful, eager to close it.

237
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:48,990
She must have fallen in the dark, sir. Felt dizzy, maybe. Girls

238
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:52,470
are weak.

239
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:56,450
Ratan does not look up from the ground. A girl does not

240
00:12:56,500 --> 00:13:00,130
trip over a thing she could step across and break her skull

241
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:03,810
on flat dirt. He stays crouched there, reading it, until the kisan

242
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:07,490
runs out of things to say and the field goes quiet around

243
00:13:07,540 --> 00:13:11,170
him.

244
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:15,230
Ratan pulls the thin file back off the closed pile and opens

245
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:18,990
it on the desk. The MUNSHI watches over his register, not understanding,

246
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:22,750
then understanding and not liking it.

247
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:25,930
Sir, that was closed yesterday. You signed it off yourself.

248
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:31,590
I'm opening it again.

249
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:35,730
For a postmortem? Sir, it's a big house's matter. Bherulal seth's. He

250
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:39,570
sent word himself to settle it fast.

251
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:42,270
So?

252
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:46,650
So... nothing, sir. Just... word will reach the top.

253
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,883
Ratan takes a fresh requisition form, writes the order across it in

254
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:52,817
his own hand, and signs it. He blots it and turns it

255
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:55,750
to face the munshi.

256
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:59,650
Send it today. The district hospital here, to Dr. Bhanwar.

257
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,737
The munshi looks at the form, and at the inspector who has

258
00:14:03,787 --> 00:14:07,523
signed papers in this room for fifteen years and never once asked

259
00:14:07,573 --> 00:14:11,310
for a postmortem on anything. He picks it up as if it

260
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:15,097
might be hot. Across the room, DEVA, at the wall, watches the

261
00:14:15,147 --> 00:14:18,883
man amend his own signature, and something in his face that had

262
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:22,670
been going out comes back a little.

263
00:14:23,020 --> 00:14:27,570
MISHRA sits behind a clean desk, a neat man, a pressed uniform,

264
00:14:27,620 --> 00:14:32,170
a glass of water and no files. He waves Ratan to a

265
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:36,770
chair with real warmth, the warmth of a man who has never

266
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:41,370
had to raise his voice to get his way.

267
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:45,150
Arre, sit, Ratan, sit. Shall I send for tea? Listen, this Koteshwar

268
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,630
file. You've sent it for a postmortem?

269
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:49,570
I have.

270
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:54,470
Twenty-five years of service, yaar. Two left. And you, over a girl

271
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:59,070
who fell — what for? Tell me, what's the matter?

272
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:00,650
The bund was knee-high.

273
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:06,070
So? People die falling from knee height too, if the head hits

274
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:11,190
wrong. Look. The file was closed. Let it stay closed. Do your

275
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:16,310
two years in peace, take your pension, go home. What's in this

276
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:21,430
mess — one girl, a big house, reach to the very top.

277
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:26,550
Let it go, brother. Not for me — for yourself.

278
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,690
It's done, Mishra. The file's gone.

279
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:31,670
For a moment the warmth is not quite there in Mishra's face.

280
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:34,350
Then it comes back, smooth.

281
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,690
Gone. All right. Have your tea before you go.

282
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,990
Ratan stands and goes without the chai. Mishra watches the door a

283
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,990
moment, then picks up the phone.

284
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:48,402
A black stone face under a heap of marigold and silver foil,

285
00:15:48,452 --> 00:15:52,514
fierce, smeared with vermilion. The PUJARI takes a bottle of country liquor,

286
00:15:52,564 --> 00:15:56,626
tips it into the shallow silver dish set below the god's mouth,

287
00:15:56,676 --> 00:16:00,738
and the level in the dish drops as they watch. DEVA, a

288
00:16:00,788 --> 00:16:04,850
step behind Ratan, stares at it.

289
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,470
Sir... it's... going down.

290
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:12,570
It's Kaal Bhairav, son. The kotwal of Avanti. Flowers don't move him

291
00:16:12,620 --> 00:16:17,370
much. No sweets, no recommendations. Only this — liquor. And whoever lies

292
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:22,170
before him, he settles the account himself. He needs no police station.

293
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:29,243
animal he respects)* इन पे फूल-पत्ती नहीं चढ़ती ज़्यादा। न मिठाई, न

294
00:16:29,293 --> 00:16:36,017
सिफ़ारिश। बस यही — दारू। और जो झूठ बोले इनके सामने, उसका

295
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:42,790
हिसाब ये ख़ुद लेते हैं। किसी थाने की ज़रूरत नहीं।

296
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:47,282
Ratan and Deva go lane to lane, and the lanes close as

297
00:16:47,332 --> 00:16:51,474
they come. A man remembers a buffalo to see to. A woman

298
00:16:51,524 --> 00:16:55,666
pulls a child inside. Doors that were open find reasons to be

299
00:16:55,716 --> 00:16:59,858
half-shut. The trade has taught this village to have nothing to say

300
00:16:59,908 --> 00:17:04,050
to a uniform that is actually asking.

301
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:07,657
At last an old WOMAN, sweeping a doorstep, talks — because she

302
00:17:07,707 --> 00:17:10,963
is too old to be afraid of anyone, and because nobody important

303
00:17:11,013 --> 00:17:14,270
listens to her anyway.

304
00:17:14,620 --> 00:17:17,610
You police have come now? The girl was burned yesterday.

305
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:20,150
Mother, was there talk of her marriage?

306
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:23,410
Talk! It was fixed. To Dhanraj seth.

307
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:26,830
Dhanraj? But... I've heard he's an old man.

308
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:29,882
Sixty, son, not a day less. But here they don't look at

309
00:17:29,932 --> 00:17:32,634
age. They look at standing. Bherulal had debt on the house —

310
00:17:32,684 --> 00:17:35,386
the licence quota hasn't been met for two years. So hand the

311
00:17:35,436 --> 00:17:38,138
girl over against the debt, into the old man's house. That's how

312
00:17:38,188 --> 00:17:40,890
it goes.

313
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:45,094
Deva turns to look at Ratan, the wrongness of it sitting on

314
00:17:45,144 --> 00:17:48,998
his young face. Ratan has gone still — the particular stillness of

315
00:17:49,048 --> 00:17:52,902
a man into whom one piece has just slid against another. He

316
00:17:52,952 --> 00:17:56,806
does not say what he is thinking. He thanks the old woman

317
00:17:56,856 --> 00:18:00,710
and turns back toward the road.

318
00:18:01,060 --> 00:18:05,863
A small, warm, plain room, lit by one tube-light. AMMA presses a

319
00:18:05,913 --> 00:18:10,717
second roti onto Deva's plate before the first is gone. MANJU sits

320
00:18:10,767 --> 00:18:15,570
to the side, her eyes down, a girl who is being discussed.

321
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:20,510
Eat, eat. You've gone thin. And listen, the boy's photo came from

322
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:25,150
Rajasthan. Good family, well-off. Manju will rule the house there. It's just

323
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:29,790
across the border, but there's a direct bus, three hours.

324
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:37,010
Deva looks at his sister. He has spent the whole day learning

325
00:18:37,060 --> 00:18:43,930
what a girl is worth in this belt, and the word

326
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,190
Manju. Have you seen the photo? Did it... seem all right to

327
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,150
you?

328
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:53,810
Whatever you all think best, brother.

329
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,030
I'm asking you. You.

330
00:18:56,380 --> 00:19:00,970
Manju glances at her mother, then down again, and says nothing, which

331
00:19:01,020 --> 00:19:05,610
is its own answer. Amma fills the silence the way mothers do.

332
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:08,790
Oh, what are you asking her for. She's shy. You just do

333
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:11,670
your job properly, the rest takes care of itself.

334
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:16,090
Deva starts to say something — about old men and young girls

335
00:19:16,140 --> 00:19:20,210
and what a marriage can be made to mean — and lets

336
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:24,330
it go. This match is a good one; it is not a

337
00:19:24,380 --> 00:19:28,450
sale. And still he cannot get the day out of his mouth.

338
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:33,590
The report is already back. The same day it went out. The

339
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:38,430
MUNSHI hands it across almost apologetically. Ratan reads it: typed, stamped, two

340
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:43,270
lines — death consistent with a fall, no foul play indicated. He

341
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:48,110
holds it and does not put it down.

342
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:52,650
The same day?

343
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,550
The doctor was quick, sir. Said it's your case, not to hold

344
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:58,150
it up.

345
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:02,223
Ratan has handed Dr. Bhanwar a dozen reports like this over the

346
00:20:02,273 --> 00:20:05,997
years, and not one of them ever took less than a week,

347
00:20:06,047 --> 00:20:09,770
because a real postmortem takes a week. He knows exactly what a

348
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:13,543
same-day clean report is, in his hands, in his ink. He spent

349
00:20:13,593 --> 00:20:17,317
twenty-five years making them. The clean page does not close the girl's

350
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:21,090
death for him. It opens everything standing behind it.

351
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:24,990
He folds the report into his pocket, and for once he is

352
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:28,590
not tired in the way he is usually tired.

353
00:20:28,940 --> 00:20:32,890
DR. BHANWAR SINGH does not get up. A tired, clean-shaven man in

354
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:36,890
a pressed shirt, a Rajput of Ratan's own age and kind, with

355
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:40,890
a room that smells of phenyl and old paper.

356
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:45,830
You'll have got the report. It's clean. Death by a fall.

357
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:47,810
How did it come back clean the same day, Bhanwar?

358
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:51,470
It was done by the rules. The same rules for twenty-five years,

359
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,830
Singh sahib. And this many of your cases were closed by these

360
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:58,190
same rules. Not once did you ask 'how, the same day.' What's

361
00:20:58,240 --> 00:21:01,550
changed today?

362
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:03,290
I don't know.

363
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:08,843
flat)* और तेरे भी इतने केस इसी नियम से बंद हुए हैं।

364
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:14,097
एक बार भी तूने नहीं पूछा "उसी दिन कैसे।" आज क्या बदल

365
00:21:14,147 --> 00:21:19,350
गया?

366
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:24,810
Go home, Singh sahib. You've two years left. Don't ruin them for

367
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:29,970
a dead girl. She isn't coming back — and neither are you.

368
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:34,930
It is the truest thing he has said in years, and it

369
00:21:34,980 --> 00:21:39,590
costs him to say it out loud. Bhanwar hears it. He does

370
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:44,250
not soften — that is Mishra's trade, not his — he answers

371
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:48,910
flat, the way he reads out a cause of death.

372
00:21:49,260 --> 00:21:52,913
No paper will help him now. Every paper in the district lies,

373
00:21:52,963 --> 00:21:56,616
and he knows it, because he taught it how. So he does

374
00:21:56,666 --> 00:22:00,319
the thing he has not done in twenty-five years. He goes out

375
00:22:00,369 --> 00:22:04,021
among the field hands at the end of the day, on foot,

376
00:22:04,071 --> 00:22:07,724
off the books, and asks — whose girl, whose house, who saw

377
00:22:07,774 --> 00:22:11,427
her last. They are afraid of the asking, and of him, and

378
00:22:11,477 --> 00:22:15,130
of the big house, all at once.

379
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:16,630
Were you in the field that night?

380
00:22:16,980 --> 00:22:19,490
I know nothing, sir. I'm a labouring man. I come at dawn,

381
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:22,050
I leave at dusk.

382
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,830
I'm not trapping you. I'm only asking.

383
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:29,503
The hand looks at him a long moment, weighing the old inspector

384
00:22:29,553 --> 00:22:33,877
against the thing everyone in the village has already agreed to forget.

385
00:22:33,927 --> 00:22:38,250
Then, quietly, giving him only the smallest true thing:

386
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,510
It's a big house over there, sir. Bherulal seth's. It's their matter.

387
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:44,470
Don't ask me.

388
00:22:44,820 --> 00:22:48,823
The name is still nothing to Ratan. He turns and looks across

389
00:22:48,873 --> 00:22:52,877
the darkening fields at the big house standing at the end of

390
00:22:52,927 --> 00:22:56,930
them, lit up, and he walks toward it.

391
00:22:57,280 --> 00:23:00,878
A prosperous house, gold in the doorway, a generator humming somewhere. Ratan

392
00:23:00,928 --> 00:23:04,526
comes up the steps with his cap in his hand — a

393
00:23:04,576 --> 00:23:08,174
policeman come to ask a family about a dead girl. He knocks.

394
00:23:08,224 --> 00:23:11,822
There are feet inside, and a bolt drawn back, and the door

395
00:23:11,872 --> 00:23:15,470
opens.

396
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:18,330
It is SUGNA.

397
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:21,870
Twenty-five years. Neither of them moves. Somewhere inside the house a woman

398
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:25,110
is crying and stops.

399
00:23:25,460 --> 00:23:26,050
Now you come.

400
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:30,750
...Sugna.

401
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:33,770
She looks at the cap in his hands, and the khaki, and

402
00:23:33,820 --> 00:23:36,490
back at his face.

403
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:39,190
You've come in uniform. To ask questions.

404
00:23:39,540 --> 00:23:42,690
I didn't know this was your house. I'm telling the truth, Sugna.

405
00:23:42,740 --> 00:23:45,890
I didn't—

406
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:48,030
When did you ever know anything.

407
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:52,524
He has no answer to that, the way he has had no

408
00:23:52,574 --> 00:23:56,719
answer to it for twenty-five years. Behind her the house is dim,

409
00:23:56,769 --> 00:24:00,913
full of people sitting in the heavy quiet that comes after a

410
00:24:00,963 --> 00:24:05,107
death. On a shelf by the door, a girl's things — a

411
00:24:05,157 --> 00:24:09,301
school bag, a comb, a folded dupatta, set aside the way you

412
00:24:09,351 --> 00:24:13,496
set aside what you cannot yet put away. He looks at them,

413
00:24:13,546 --> 00:24:17,690
and at his sister's closed face, and it begins to come.

414
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,510
Whose... whose girl was she?

415
00:24:19,860 --> 00:24:24,890
Sugna's jaw works. She will not say it. From inside, an AUNT's

416
00:24:24,940 --> 00:24:29,970
voice, taking the policeman at the door for only a policeman:

417
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:31,054
The name goes into him and does not stop. Leela was his

418
00:24:31,104 --> 00:24:31,838
sister's daughter. He read the first line of that file and signed

419
00:24:31,888 --> 00:24:32,622
it a fall and never turned to the name on the second

420
00:24:32,672 --> 00:24:33,406
page; he took the day's money and went home and ate his

421
00:24:33,456 --> 00:24:34,190
dinner.

422
00:24:34,540 --> 00:24:38,050
He cannot say it. She stands and watches him not say it.

423
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:41,610
BHERULAL fills the inner doorway then — heavy, still, taking in the

424
00:24:41,660 --> 00:24:45,170
brother-in-law in the uniform standing at his door at the worst hour

425
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:48,730
he could have come.

426
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:49,910
I...

427
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:50,930
You what?

428
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:55,030
She steps back from the door — not to let him in,

429
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:58,830
but because she is done holding it open — and turns into

430
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:02,630
the mourning house, and leaves him on the step with her husband's

431
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:06,430
eyes on him.

432
00:25:06,780 --> 00:25:09,130
Who is it? ...Oh.

433
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:11,750
My brother. He's in the police. Hasn't come in twenty-five years. Today

434
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:14,070
he's come.

435
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:32,857
A side room, away from the mourners. Bherulal sits Ratan down and

436
00:25:32,907 --> 00:25:36,883
sits across from him. He is not grieving in front of Ratan;

437
00:25:36,933 --> 00:25:40,910
he is working out a problem, and Ratan is the problem.

438
00:25:41,260 --> 00:25:44,110
Twenty-five years you didn't show your face at this house. You're Sugna's

439
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:47,010
brother, and you didn't come for the wedding, didn't come when the

440
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:49,910
daughters were born, nothing. And today, this very night, here you are.

441
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:52,810
In uniform.

442
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,470
How did the girl die, Bherulal?

443
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:58,223
What's done is done. Leela's gone. What comes back from that? Now

444
00:25:58,273 --> 00:26:01,677
if the police come, a postmortem, word spreads — whose loss is

445
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:05,130
it? Your sister's. This house's. The little one, four years old. The

446
00:26:05,180 --> 00:26:08,583
licence is to be made in his name next year. For that

447
00:26:08,633 --> 00:26:12,037
the family name must be clean. You don't sink a living child's

448
00:26:12,087 --> 00:26:15,490
future for a dead girl.

449
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:20,750
आए, कुछ नहीं। *(he lets that sit)* और आज, इसी रात, चले

450
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:25,710
आए। वर्दी पहन के।

451
00:26:26,060 --> 00:26:28,303
Accidents keep happening in these parts, sir. A man goes out at

452
00:26:28,353 --> 00:26:30,597
night, the bike slips, that's all. It happens. You know that well

453
00:26:30,647 --> 00:26:32,890
enough.

454
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:40,190
Ratan says nothing. From the side, by the door, one of Bherulal's

455
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:47,190
MEN speaks — easy, flat, the way you'd mention the weather.

456
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:52,023
A glass of doda water goes cold at his elbow — the

457
00:26:52,073 --> 00:26:56,557
poppy-husk brew he drinks to put the days down. Tonight it does

458
00:26:56,607 --> 00:27:01,090
not work. On the table in front of him are two papers.

459
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:05,623
One is the clean report, his way out, the honourable one: he

460
00:27:05,673 --> 00:27:10,157
did his duty, it is official, he can stop now and keep

461
00:27:10,207 --> 00:27:14,690
his pension and his life. The other is a blank requisition form.

462
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:19,047
He turns his hand over. The pale band where the ring used

463
00:27:19,097 --> 00:27:23,104
to be is white in the lamplight. Down the passage, KANTA appears

464
00:27:23,154 --> 00:27:27,161
in her doorway in her nightclothes and sees him sitting up over

465
00:27:27,211 --> 00:27:31,219
papers at this hour, which he has not done in years. She

466
00:27:31,269 --> 00:27:35,276
does not ask. She knows the shape of him well enough to

467
00:27:35,326 --> 00:27:39,333
know it is not a thing he will say. She goes back

468
00:27:39,383 --> 00:27:43,390
in and the light under her door goes out.

469
00:27:43,740 --> 00:27:46,383
He does not pick up the pen for a long time. Outside,

470
00:27:46,433 --> 00:27:49,077
the night thins toward grey. And then, near morning, he picks it

471
00:27:49,127 --> 00:27:51,770
up.

472
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:56,321
The post is empty and grey, the fan still. Ratan writes out

473
00:27:56,371 --> 00:28:00,573
a fresh requisition by hand — a second postmortem, this one at

474
00:28:00,623 --> 00:28:04,824
the district headquarters hospital two hundred kilometres away, out of Bhanwar's reach,

475
00:28:04,874 --> 00:28:09,076
and Mishra's, and the big house's. At the bottom he does not

476
00:28:09,126 --> 00:28:13,327
press the office stamp into it. He signs it himself, his own

477
00:28:13,377 --> 00:28:17,579
name, in full, the way a man signs a thing he means

478
00:28:17,629 --> 00:28:21,830
to stand behind.

479
00:28:22,180 --> 00:28:26,730
DEVA comes in early, the dawn grey behind him, and stops when

480
00:28:26,780 --> 00:28:31,330
he sees the old man already at the desk. He sees what

481
00:28:31,380 --> 00:28:35,930
the requisition is, and the name on it, and what it will

482
00:28:35,980 --> 00:28:40,530
cost. He does not say anything. He stands a little straighter.

483
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:44,510
Ratan caps the pen and sets it down. He has the look

484
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:48,190
of a man who has finally decided something.

485
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:51,370
CUT TO BLACK.
